Visualizations : \
Children (and adults!) process visual data much better than rows of numbers. Focus on these three charts for their dashboard:\
The "Where Does My Money Go?" Pie Chart: A breakdown of their gross income. It should clearly show slices for Rent, Taxes, Savings, Debt Repayment, and Discretionary Spending. This visually reinforces how much of their paycheck is actually theirs to spend.\
The Net Worth Line Graph: A line moving up and to the right over time. This includes their cash plus their savings, minus their loans. If they take out a big loan, they will see this line drop, which is a powerful visual lesson.\
The Credit Score Gauge: A colour-coded gauge (Red, Yellow, Green) that shows their current standing. Use Credit Report Card instead of Credit Score as report card is more child focused. \
\
A graph to show the magic of compounding on their savings\
